Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a private residence in Durham, North Carolina, thanking the host and praising the work of Diane, Mark, Marica, and Jaime Harrison. She emphasized the importance of democracy and the need to be vigilant in protecting it. Harris highlighted the accomplishments of the Biden administration, including the extension of the Child Tax Credit, tax cuts for families, infrastructure investments, climate crisis solutions, and job creation. She stressed the significance of elections and the impact they have on issues such as voting rights and LGBTQ rights. Harris urged support for Joe Biden and emphasized the need to hold on to Senate and House seats, as well as gubernatorial and secretary of state positions. She encouraged grassroots organizing and reminded people of their power to shape the outcome of elections.